'''New York State Route&nbsp;116''' ('''NY&nbsp;116''') is an 8.12-mile (13&nbsp;km) long east&ndash;west state highway in [[Westchester County, New York]], in the [[United States]]. It begins in the hamlet of [[Somers, New York|Somers]] (located in the town of the same name) and continues into the state of [[Connecticut]] as [[Route 116 (Connecticut)|Route&nbsp;116]].

==Route description==
[[Image:Titicus Reservoir.jpg|left|thumb|Titicus Reservoir from Route&nbsp;116]]
NY&nbsp;116 begins near the northern terminus of [[New York State Route 100|NY&nbsp;100]] at [[U.S. Route&nbsp;202]] in the hamlet of [[Somers, New York|Somers]] as Purdys Road. It heads east into the town of [[North Salem, New York|North Salem]], where it has junctions with [[Interstate&nbsp;684]] and [[New York State Route 22|NY&nbsp;22]] in the hamlet of [[Purdys, New York|Purdys]], just after crossing the town line. In [[North Salem, New York|North Salem]], it is known as Titicus Road, running north of the [[Titicus Reservoir]], serving the hamlets of [[Salem Center, New York|Salem Center]] and North Salem. It has an [[overlap (road)|overlap]] with [[New York State Route 121|NY&nbsp;121]] a mile before crossing the Connecticut state line. The route progresses eastward, crossing the state line and continuing as [[Route 116 (Connecticut)|Route&nbsp;116]].

==History==
NY&nbsp;116 was originally a much longer route when it was assigned as part of the [[1930 state highway renumbering (New York)|1930 renumbering of state highways in New York]]. At the time, it began in [[Peekskill, New York|Peekskill]] and followed modern [[U.S. Route 202 (New York)|U.S. Route&nbsp;202]] east to [[Somers, New York|Somers]],<ref name="1930map">{{cite map |title=Road Map of New York |year=1930 |publisher=[[Standard Oil Company of New York]] |cartography=[[General Drafting]]}}</ref> from where it continued east over its current alignment to the [[Connecticut]] state line.<ref>{{cite map |title=Texaco Road Map <U+2013> New York |publisher=[[Texas Oil Company]] |year=1932 |cartography=[[Rand McNally and Company]]}}</ref> In 1934, US&nbsp;202 was designated and [[overlap (road)|overlap]]ped with NY&nbsp;116 from Peekskill to Somers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fhwa.dot.gov/infrastructure/us202.cfm |title=U.S. 202 <U+2013> Maine to Delaware |last=Weingroff |first=Richard |date=January 9, 2009 |work=Highway History |publisher=[[Federal Highway Administration]] |accessdate=March 31, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite map |title=Road Map & Historical Guide <U+2013> New York |publisher=[[Sun Oil Company]] |year=1935 |cartography=[[Rand McNally and Company]]}}</ref> The overlap was eliminated by 1938 when NY&nbsp;116 was truncated to its current western terminus in Somers.<ref>{{cite book |last=Thibodeau |first=William A. |title=The ALA Green Book |edition=1938<U+2013>39 |year=1938 |publisher=Automobile Legal Association}}</ref>

